Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
extractRC(25.10)                                              extractRC(25.10)

Name
       extractRC

Syntax
       extractRC

       [-help]

       Extracts  resistance  and  capacitance for the interconnects and stores
       the results in an RC database. Optionally, an ASCII report file can  be
       generated.  Use  this  command after performing early global routing or
       final routing, and after using the setExtractRCMode command.

Parameter
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the extractRC command. For a  de-
              tailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man extractRC

       Example

       The following command extracts interconnect resistance and capacitance:

       extractRC

       RC database is created.

       The  extractRC  command can be followed by the rcOut command to extract
       the parasitics from the RC database, and to generate  an  ASCII  report
       containing the database information.

Related Information
              * setExtractRCMode

              * The following chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                     * RC Extraction

